## 3. App Router vs Pages Router Analysis

### 3.1 Recommendation: **App Router (Definitive)**

**App Router is the correct choice for NuttyFans** for the following reasons:

### 3.2 Comparison Matrix

| Factor | App Router | Pages Router | Winner |
|--------|------------|--------------|--------|
| **Future Direction** | Active development by Vercel | Maintenance mode | App Router ✓ |
| **Server Components** | Native support (default) | Not supported | App Router ✓ |
| **Performance** | Better (streaming, partial rendering) | Good | App Router ✓ |
| **SEO** | Excellent (metadata API) | Good | App Router ✓ |
| **Layouts** | Nested layouts (native) | Manual implementation | App Router ✓ |
| **Data Fetching** | Simpler (async components) | getServerSideProps/getStaticProps | App Router ✓ |
| **Bundle Size** | Smaller (server components) | Larger (all client) | App Router ✓ |
| **Learning Curve** | Steeper initially | Gentler | Pages Router |
| **Ecosystem Maturity** | Growing rapidly | Mature | Pages Router |
| **Long-term Viability** | 5+ years | Likely deprecated | App Router ✓ |

### 3.3 Long-term Justification

| Consideration | Analysis |
|---------------|----------|
| **Vercel Investment** | Vercel is investing heavily in App Router; it is the strategic direction |
| **React 19 Alignment** | App Router leverages React 19 Server Components natively |
| **Performance at Scale** | Server Components reduce JS bundle sent to client — critical for NuttyFans media-heavy pages |
| **SEO Requirements** | NuttyFans needs strong SEO for creator discovery; App Router's metadata API is superior |
| **Streaming Support** | Live streaming features will benefit from React Suspense/streaming |
| **Deprecation Risk** | Pages Router will likely enter deprecation within 2-3 years |

### 3.4 Risk Mitigation

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Some libraries not yet App Router compatible | Check compatibility before adding dependencies |
| Team learning curve | App Router patterns documented in codebase rules |
| Edge cases in routing | Follow Vercel's official patterns |

### 3.5 Decision

> **Use App Router exclusively. Do not mix with Pages Router.**

This aligns with:
- `docs/03-TECHNICAL-ARCHITECTURE.md` (already specifies App Router)
- `rules/PROJECT_RULES.md` P6 (Next.js App Router)

